## Strict phase gate

Phases are **sequential and mandatory**. Never skip phase 2, phase 3, or phase 4. Never skip phase 6 before `done`.

```
planned → architecture-ready → tasks-ready → approved → in-progress → review-ready → done
  (PO)      (Architect)         (Modeller)   (human)    (squad)       (reviewers)    (human)
```

| Action | Phase | Allowed edits |
|--------|-------|----------------|
| Feature analysis, **FQ*n*** | 1 | `feature/*.md`, `docs/**` (not domain-spec yet unless PO delegates) |
| Domain vocabulary | 1b | `docs/domain-specification.md`, `feature/*.md` |
| Architecture, **AQ*n***, HTMX model, ADR drafts | 2 | `feature/*.md`, `docs/**` (incl. `docs/adr/`, `docs/htmx-events.md`), domain spec |
| Answer **FQ*n*** or **AQ*n*** | 1 or 2 | `feature/*.md`, `docs/**` only — **not** `src/main/**`, `src/test/**` |
| Task break | 3 | `feature/*.md` |
| User approves task IDs | 4 | `feature/*.md` (record approval) |
| Squad development (TDD) | 5 | `src/main/**`, `src/test/**`, templates, CSS/JS, docs as needed |
| Code review (readonly) | 6 | `feature/*.md` (Review findings only); squad fixes blockers |
| User review approval | 7 | `feature/*.md` (record **Review approval**); set `done` |

### Exempt changes (skip full pipeline)

Typo, comment-only, formatter, docs-only with **no behaviour, schema, or cross-package impact** — per [change-request-analysis.mdc](change-request-analysis.mdc). Still run [static-analysis.mdc](static-analysis.mdc) when code touched.

### Open question kinds

| Kind | Prefix | Phase | Decides |
|------|--------|-------|---------|
| **Feature question** | **FQ*n*** | 1 | Product scope, UX, wireframe, domain rules, user-visible behaviour |
| **Architecture question** | **AQ*n*** | 2 | Packages, layers, routes, schema, HTMX, libraries, cross-context integration |

Legacy undifferentiated **Q*n*** in existing feature docs are treated as **FQ*n*** until updated.

### Answering open questions ≠ development approval

**Forbidden:** starting phase 5 because the user answered **FQ1**, **AQ2**, chose an option, said "yes"/"big-bang", or clarified scope. Those actions only update the relevant questions table (status `answered`, **Answer** column) — they do **not** authorize coding.

### Manual acceptance only — ADR, tasks, review, done (mandatory)

**An agent never accepts an ADR, approves tasks, approves review, or marks `done` on its own.**

| Artefact | Agent may | User only |
|----------|-----------|-----------|
| **ADR** | `Proposed`, `Under Review`, `Reopened`; fill Recommendation | **`Accepted`**, **`Rejected`**, **`Superseded`**, **`Reopened`** |
| **Feature (changelog)** | Phases 1–3; status up to `tasks-ready`; set `review-ready` after squad + verify | **Phase 4:** approve task IDs; **Phase 7:** review approval + `done` |
| **FQ/AQ** | Record answer **if the user provided it** | Treat agent guesses as acceptance |

**Counts as ADR acceptance:** "Aceito o ADR-0009", "Aprovo o ADR 0009", "ADR-0009 accepted".

**Counts as development approval (phase 4):** "Approve T1–T8", "Go ahead with T1-java, T2-htmx".

**Counts as review approval (phase 7):** "Review approved", "Mark done".

**Does not count as approval:** "implement it" without task IDs; ADR accepted without task IDs; silence after FQ/AQ answers; reviewers clearing their own blockers without user sign-off on `done`.

Detail: [adr.mdc](adr.mdc).

### Impact review when answering open questions (mandatory)

Every time the user answers **FQ*n*** or **AQ*n***, the **Product Owner** or **Architect** agent **must** run an **impact review**:

1. **Record** the answer in the correct table.
2. **Re-read and update** the feature doc: Impact, changelog cross-impacts, Risks, **Wireframe**, **Architecture**, **HTMX component model**, **ADRs**, **Feature checklist**, **Tasks**, **Test coverage**, [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md), [docs/feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md), [`dev-import.sql`](../../src/main/resources/dev-import.sql), [docs/htmx-events.md](../../docs/htmx-events.md), [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) §9.
3. **May open new questions** — add **FQ*n+1** or **AQ*n+1** with status `open`.
4. **Present** impact deltas; do not assume silence means approval.
5. If blocking questions remain `open`, **stop** for phase 4.

## Working code invariant

**No development ends with non-working code.** The tree must compile, tests must pass for the scope touched, and the app must remain runnable.

| Situation | Required action |
|-----------|-----------------|
| Task or session ending | `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B verify` green — see [static-analysis.mdc](static-analysis.mdc) |
| Approved tasks incomplete | Keep changelog **`in-progress`** — never `review-ready` or `done` |
| Review blockers open | Keep **`review-ready`**; squad fixes; re-run reviewers on blockers |
| Partial work breaks build/tests | Fix forward **or** revert — do not stop on red |
| Cannot finish in one session | Leave **`in-progress`** or **`review-ready`** with Implementation notes; workspace still **green** |

**Forbidden:** marking `done` with failing tests; `@Disabled` or weakened assertions to fake green.

## Seven phases

```
1. Feature analysis (PO)  →  1b. Domain model  →  2. Architecture (Architect)
  →  3. Task break (Modeller)  →  4. Development approved (human)
  →  5. Development squad (Java → HTMX → JS per task)  →  6. Review (readonly trio)
  →  7. Review approved + done (human)
```

| Phase | Primary agent | Agent must not |
|-------|---------------|----------------|
| **1. Feature analysis** | Product Owner | Write `src/**`; answer FQ*n* without user; skip architecture |
| **1b. Domain model** | Domain Model | Write `src/**`; skip when no vocabulary change (record "N/A") |
| **2. Architecture** | Architect | Start implementation; skip HTMX model or `htmx-events.md` delta |
| **3. Task break** | Task Modeller | Start implementation; omit layer tags or TC mapping |
| **4. Development approved** | Human | — |
| **5. Development squad** | Java / HTMX / JS Developers | Skip tests; implement unapproved tasks; JS without Architect justification |
| **6. Review** | Java / HTMX / JS Reviewers | Edit production code (findings only in feature doc) |
| **7. Done** | Human + Docs Sync | Set `done` without review approval and verify green |

## Phase 1 — Feature analysis (Product Owner Agent)

Required when: new behaviour, route, schema, multi-package refactor, or bug fix with cross-feature impact.

1. Resolve `<feature-slug>` — [change-request-analysis.mdc](change-request-analysis.mdc) §0.
2. Create or extend `feature/<feature-slug>.md` with Summary, **Wireframe** (when UI), Impact, Risks, changelog entry (`status: planned`).
3. Build **Feature checklist** (**FC1**, **FC2**, …, **FCdev**).
4. Open **FQ*n*** for user flows, edge cases, roles, cross-feature impact, UI copy. **Do not answer** — status `open` until user responds.
5. Be critical: ask where changes affect other features, auth, SEO, notifications, messaging, etc.

**Exit criteria:** Impact and Wireframe filled; blocking **FQ*n*** resolved. **No code.** Hand off to Domain Model Agent (phase 1b).

## Phase 1b — Domain model (Domain Model Agent)

1. Read [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) and the feature doc.
2. If vocabulary or invariants change: update Ubiquitous Language in domain-spec **before** architecture.
3. If no change: record **Domain model: N/A** in the changelog entry.

**Exit criteria:** domain-spec current or N/A recorded. Hand off to Architect Agent (phase 2).

## Phase 2 — Architecture design (Architect Agent)

Detail: [architecture-design.mdc](architecture-design.mdc), [adr.mdc](adr.mdc).

1. Confirm compliance with Accepted ADRs in [docs/adr/README.md](../../docs/adr/README.md).
2. Create/update ADRs for transversal **AQ*n*** answers (`Proposed` only).
3. Add `## Architecture` on the feature doc — ADR links, packages, routes, schema, templates, tests.
4. Build **`### HTMX component model`** — per Wireframe screen: component id, fragment route, activator, target/swap, events out/in, JS companion (`none` or module), auth allowlist row needed.
5. Add **`### HTMX interaction diagram`** when flows cross multiple components.
6. Draft updates to [docs/htmx-events.md](../../docs/htmx-events.md) when adding custom events, auth allowlist rows, scoped refresh patterns, or JS lifecycle coupling.
7. Track **AQ*n*** (schema, libraries, bounded contexts, HTMX mechanism choice); run impact review after each answer.
8. Validate against [contraponto-layered-architecture.mdc](contraponto-layered-architecture.mdc), [contraponto-bounded-contexts.mdc](contraponto-bounded-contexts.mdc), [htmx-events.md](../../docs/htmx-events.md).
9. Set **Status:** `architecture-ready`. **Stop** for manual ADR acceptance.

**Exit criteria:** Architecture + HTMX model complete; `htmx-events.md` delta identified; blocking **AQ*n*** resolved; status `architecture-ready`. **No code.**

## Phase 3 — Task break (Task Modeller Agent)

Read: feature doc, domain-spec, Accepted ADRs, Architecture, HTMX component model.

Add to changelog entry:

- **Feature checklist** — extend **FC*n***; always **FCdev** for `dev-import.sql`.
- **Tasks** — layer-tagged, ordered, small:
  - `T*n*-java` — entity, repo, service, endpoint, Flyway, `HtmxTriggers`, `Toast`
  - `T*n*-htmx` — Qute templates, `hx-*`, OOB, navigation attrs (depends on paired `*-java`)
  - `T*n*-js` — only when Architect marked JS required (depends on paired `*-htmx`)
  - **Tdev** — `dev-import.sql` + feature-catalog § Dev personas
- **Test coverage** — **TC*n*** mapped to tasks: `unit`, `rest` (HX headers), `web` (`@WebTest`), `htmx-contract`, `arch`

Each task row: **Depends**, **Expected outcome** (domain language), **Tests**.

Set **Status:** `tasks-ready`. **Stop — do not implement.**

## Phase 4 — Development approved (human)

Record:

```markdown
**Development approval:** approved YYYY-MM-DD — tasks: T1-java, T1-htmx, T2-java, …
```

Set **Status:** `approved`. Implement **only** approved task IDs.

## Phase 5 — Development squad (Java → HTMX → JS per task)

**Precondition:** status `approved` with **Development approval** line.

Set **Status:** `in-progress`. For **each approved task block** in order:

### Per-task execution order

1. **Java Developer** — Red → Green → Refactor on `T*n*-java` (may delegate to `tdd-red`, `tdd-green`, `tdd-refactor`).
2. **HTMX Developer** — templates for `T*n*-htmx`; follows Architect HTMX model row-by-row.
3. **Javascript Developer** — `T*n*-js` only when Architect marked JS required; HTMX-first — no duplicate `htmx.ajax` of template `hx-get`.
4. Run mapped **TC*n*** tests; mark task rows and FC rows when verified.
5. **Tdev** + **FCdev** before leaving phase 5.

### Squad alignment rules

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Contract handoff | Java exposes paths, fragment ids, OOB targets, `HtmxTriggers`; HTMX consumes; JS listens with `evt.detail?.target` guards |
| Routes | Templates use `*Paths` / `TemplateExtensions.url` — not hardcoded endpoint strings |
| Events | New custom event → `HtmxTriggers.java` + template subscriber + `htmx-events.md` |
| Forbidden | Full pages from `/forms/*`; `window.location.reload()` on auth; unscoped `#main` refresh on auth |

**End of phase 5:** all approved tasks checked; `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B verify` green; set **`review-ready`**.

## Phase 6 — Review (readonly trio)

**Precondition:** status `review-ready`; verify green.

Run **in parallel** (readonly):

| Reviewer | Focus |
|----------|-------|
| **Java Code Reviewer** | Layering, bounded contexts, auth, `HtmxTriggers`/`Toast`, tests, Spotless |
| **HTMX Reviewer** | HTMX model vs templates, `htmx-events.md`, scoped refresh, allowlist, navigation, confirm modals, SEO |
| **Javascript Reviewer** | Necessity (HTMX-first), module quality, swap guards, i18n, load order |

Record findings in changelog:

```markdown
#### Review findings

| Reviewer | Severity | Location | Finding | Status |
|----------|----------|----------|---------|--------|
| HTMX | blocker | path | … | open / fixed / waived |
```

**Severity:** `blocker` (must fix before `done`) | `suggestion` (user may waive).

**Squad** fixes `blocker` findings; re-run affected reviewer. **Reviewers must not** edit `src/**` directly.

**Exit criteria:** no open `blocker` findings (or user waived suggestions explicitly).

## Phase 7 — Review approved + done (human + Docs Sync)

Record:

```markdown
**Review approval:** approved YYYY-MM-DD
```

**Docs Sync** agent updates feature-catalog, README, ARCHITECTURE, final `htmx-events.md` if not done in phase 2/5.

**Feature checklist recheck (mandatory):** walk every **FC*n*** row.

**Finish (all required):**

1. Approved tasks and test coverage checked off.
2. Feature checklist recheck complete (including **FCdev**).
3. `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B verify` passes.
4. `ReadLints` clean on edited paths.
5. Docs per [documentation.mdc](documentation.mdc); **Implementation notes** filled.
6. **Review approval** recorded; set **`done`** only after 1–5.

## Status values

| Status | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `planned` | Feature analysis in progress |
| `architecture-ready` | Architecture + HTMX model complete; ready for task break |
| `tasks-ready` | Awaiting task approval |
| `approved` | User approved tasks; no code yet |
| `in-progress` | Squad development — **must leave repo working** at session end |
| `review-ready` | Implementation complete; awaiting review |
| `done` | Review approved; FC rechecked; **verify green** |

